  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-07-06",
    "date": "2023-11-13T19:31:36Z",
    "text": "Freeing Americans Detained Abroad Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of State to dedicate resources to assist U.S. citizens detained or kidnapped overseas. The State Department must\n\n display, on a public website, a list of resources (including legal services offered pro bono or with payment) that U.S. citizens detained or kidnapped overseas may be eligible to receive; train all Foreign Service officers posted overseas on identifying and assisting detained and arbitrarily detained U.S. citizens; and designate at least one Foreign Service officer at each overseas diplomatic or consular post as a hostage affairs officer."
